Release Info

All it takes is the swipe of a finger. We connect with friends. We buy
the latest gadgets and gear. We find out what's happening in the world.
But with that same simple swipe, we cast an increasingly expansive
shadow. With each connection, we leave a digital trail that tracks
our every move and milestone, our every like and dislike. And it's
not just people. Today, all major cities are networked. Urban
infrastructures are monitored and controlled by complex operating
systems
